    • Method Detail

      • train

        void train(String trainingLabel,
           Iterable<? extends ILabeledDataWindow<DATA>> data)
    throws AISPException
        Train this instance of the classify on the given labeled data. This is not an update and instead should effectively reset the model to its initial state before training on the given data. Upon return, the instance is ready to have its IFixedClassifier.classify(org.eng.aisp.IDataWindow) method called to classify new data.
        Parameters:
        label - on which to train the model.
        data - labeled data to train the model. Data must contain at enough data with the given label for the model to be trained.
        Throws:
        AISPException - not enough date, etc.

      • parseMultiLabels

        static String[] parseMultiLabels(String multiLabelTrainingLabel)
        Parse the single string that specified multiple labels into an array of those labels. Labels are separated by commas with no spaces.
        Parameters:
        multiLabelTrainingLabel -
        Returns:
        an array of length 1 or more.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a comma-separated list of values produces zero or empty label names.
